.\" Man page for lmm update
.TH LMM-UPDATE 1 "2026-01-29" "lmm" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lmm update \- Check for and apply mod updates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lmm update
[\fIMOD_ID\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B lmm update rollback
\fIMOD_ID\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check installed mods for updates from the source (e.g. NexusMods). Without a mod ID,
checks all installed mods; with a mod ID, updates only that mod. Update policies
(notify, auto, pinned) control whether updates are applied automatically.
Changelogs are shown when available.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-game\fR=ID
Game ID (required unless default is set).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-profile\fR=NAME
Profile to check (default: active profile).
.TP
.B \-\-all
Apply all available updates (for mods with auto or notify policy).
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Show what would update without applying.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Continue even if hooks fail.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output available updates in JSON (game_id, profile, updates array).
.SH SUBCOMMAND
.TP
.B rollback \fIMOD_ID\fR
Revert a mod to its previous version. The previous version must still be in the cache.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lmm (1),
.BR lmm-install (1),
.BR lmm-mod (1).
